  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "Habeas corpus — literally \u0026ldquo;you shall have the body\u0026rdquo; — is a legal procedure that allows a person held in custody to challenge the legality of their detention before a court. It is the most direct mechanism by which the judiciary checks the executive\u0026rsquo;s power to imprison. When a court issues a writ of habeas corpus, it orders the detaining authority to produce the prisoner and justify the detention. If the justification is legally insufficient, the court orders release.\n",
